## Import .csv data to Heidi:
1. Open the .csv file in UE
2. Convert to hexadecimal display: Control + H
3. Convert empty fileds to '\N'
   Control + R (replace)
   2C 2C --> 2C 5C 4E 2C, e.g. ,, --> ,\N,
   2C 0D 0A --> 2C 5C 4E 0D 0A, e.g. ,\r\n --> ,\N\r\n
4. Import .csv file, with lines terminated by \r\n

## Open a .db file:
## Reference: http://johnatten.com/2014/12/07/installing-and-using-sqlite-on-windows/#Getting-Started---Using-SQLite-on-Windows
1. Download the sqlite3 (including sqlite.def, sqlite3.dll, sqlite3.exe, add the path to environment variables)
2. In command prompt, cd to the directory with .db file
3. Type commands:
   sqlite3
   .open DBNAME.db
   .tables
   select * from TABLENAME limit 10
4. GUI-Based Tools: sqlitebrowser

## Access and manipulate data
1. Create a table (by copying another table):
   CREATE TABLE TABLENAME AS
   SELECT * FROM TABLETAMPLATE;
2. Delete all rows in a table:
   DELETE FROM TABLENAME;
